SCANBAD

Description:

This program reads the specified files and reports on any errors that
are encountered.

Synopsis:

$ scannad <file(s)> [-m <maxbad>] [-V]

where:

<file(s)>	file(s) to scan
-m <maxbad>	maximum number of bad blocks on a file before exiting
-V		print command version to standard-error and then exit

